text:
OP, you can also take some time to onboard. Enjoy the process. There's a unique mindset when you first start. Consider taking advantage of that. I know we all want to ramp up fast and feel 'confident'. But by really owning this sponge state, you can make sure you build good habits around being an engineer and teammate.

For me personally, I try not to be productive code wise the first few weeks to focus on building a rapport with team mates. The parent org. My Skip's and so on.
